com.iasmar.rome.util.schedulers

Interface BaseSchedulerProvider

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ImmediateSchedulerProvider, SchedulerProvider

    public interface BaseSchedulerProvider
    Created by Asmar on 01/7/2018.

    Allow providing different types of Schedulers.

    Since:
    1.0
    See Also:
    Scheduler

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      io.reactivex.Scheduler computation()
      Returns a default, shared Scheduler instance intended for computational work.
      io.reactivex.Scheduler io()
      Returns a default, shared Scheduler instance intended for IO-bound work.
      io.reactivex.Scheduler ui()
      Returns a default, shared Scheduler instance intended for UI work.

    • Method Detail

      • computation

        @NonNull
io.reactivex.Scheduler computation()
        Returns a default, shared Scheduler instance intended for computational work.

        This can be used for event-loops, processing callbacks and other computational work.

        It is not recommended to perform blocking, IO-bound work on this scheduler. Use io() instead.

        Returns:
        a Scheduler meant for computation-bound work.

      • io

        @NonNull
io.reactivex.Scheduler io()
        Returns a default, shared Scheduler instance intended for IO-bound work.

        This can be used for asynchronously performing blocking IO.

        Returns:
        a Scheduler meant for IO-bound work.

      • ui

        @NonNull
io.reactivex.Scheduler ui()
        Returns a default, shared Scheduler instance intended for UI work.
        Returns:
        A Scheduler which executes actions on the Android main thread.
